710209f-a.title: Manhattan: 8th Avenue - 51st Street (West)
710209f-a.text:
Eighth Ave., south from but not including West 51st Street, showing
W.P.A. employees removing street car tracks. On the right, between 50th
and 49th Streets appears the Madison Square Garden.
May 5, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.

710212f-a.title: Manhattan: 8th Avenue - 51st Street (West)
710212f-a.text:
Eighth Ave., north from West 51st Street, showing the W.P.A. removing
car tracks and cobblestones. Note on West 53rd Street, a station of the
Sixth Ave. Elevated Line.
May 5, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
